#L_D3_msg00=My, we have some VIP guests here! Now, what would you like, corporators? An execution or a romantic jail tour followed by an execution?
#L_D3_ans00=Calm down, officer, we're only traders.
#L_D3_msg10=Oh yes, why didn't I think of that, looking at all your guns and escort? Don't move, I'm calling for backup.
#L_D3_ans10=Officer, any examination will prove we're traders. And you might get scolded for letting Cleric go. He's wanted all over the Empire. Do you read makes at all?
#L_D3_ans11=Officer, any examination will prove we're traders. If you're disturbed by our visit to the InoCo's space, remember the treaty between the Empire and the FTU giving traders free passage whatever the destination. Come on, officer. You wouldn't want to flush a document signed by the emperor himself down the drain, would you?
#L_D3_ans12=Wait! Don't call any backups. Officer, we are traders, any examination will prove it. But being a businessman, I value my time. So here's my offer: you help us find and eliminate the criminal named Cleric, and I will make up for your efforts with 100,000 credits. I'm not going to make another offer.
#L_D3_msg20=Whoa, is Cleric here? Boys, we have work to do.
#L_D3_ans20=(Dalej)
#L_D3_msg30=Oh dammit, boss. We gave them our guy on a plate!
#L_D3_ans30=Easy now, Greyhair. Let the thick skulls do some of our work and find that bastard for us. Then we'll act on circumstances.|Jana, can you eavesdrop on the patrol frequency?
